Command Line Arguments (For input file read and stored)
**********************
Acceptable inputs: A file with .txt extension that exist in main directory. Only one command line argument
Unacceptable inputs: wrong file name, no (.txt) extension.


Menu Loop 
***********
Acceptable inputs: 1(for add), 2(for search), and 3, q, QUIT, quit, Quit, Q (for quit and printing out the result to a text file).
All other inputs invalid: Prompt error message.

*Enter Option 1, a, add, ADD, Add                     PASS
*Enter Option 2, s, Search, SEARCH, search, S         PASS
*Enter Option 3, q, Q, quit, Quit, QUIT               PASS

Appropriate message appears:
*Enter Out of Bounds (0, -10, 5)                      PASS
*Enter Improper Format (String, Double)               PASS
*Enter Repeat Number (11, 22, 33)             	      PASS

Add
***
Item to add: book or electronic
-------------
Acceptable Input: 1 and 2 only
All other inputs invalid: Prompt message “Please enter numbers only:”

*Enter 1 or 2                            PASS
*Enter Improper String (wsd, hmoe)       REPEAT PROMPT — PASS
*Enter Improper Format (1.1, 0, -1)      REPEAT PROMPT — PASS

Enter Specs for book
********************
ID
---
Acceptable Input: 6 digit numbers
All other inputs invalid: Prompt message “Wrong input.Try again”

*Enter six digit numbers                              PASS
*Enter Improper String (wsd, hmoeqedqdq wow)          ERROR MESSAGE - REPEAT PROMPT	
*Enter Improper Format (1.1, 0, -1)      	      ERROR MESSAGE - REPEAT PROMPT

NAME
---
Acceptable Input: NUMBERS, STRINGS, DOUBLES, INTEGERS
